question: Which of the following state does not have 100 percent Aadhar saturation?
explanation: There are in total six states which have achieved 100 percent Aadhaar card saturation. These are Himachal Pradesh, Delhi, Telangana, Haryana, Punjab and Chandigarh .Haryana achieved saturation on September 26, 2016 followed by Punjab on October 17, 2016, Chandigarh on November 29, 2016 and Himachal Pradesh on December 8, 2016.
